text: This comment section is simply disgusting and quite frankly worrying. All of you, degrading other human beings for something as trivial and irrelevant as the colour of their skin....You 'people' may have the same anatomy as us, you may even look like us, but I do not class you as 'people'...you are less than that.   I like to believe that deep down even the worst 'people' to have lived are fundamentally kind at heart, and that this natural human kind-heartedness was lost due to upbringing, bad experiences, corruption, whatever it may be. But those like you racists make me seriously doubt this...  This world, us humans, could be so much more if we all respected one another as equals, no matter one's skin colour or heritage, no matter one's religion. Yet, this endless cycle of hate and discrimination plagues us and causes war, violence, loss and sadness, thus creating more hate and a new cycle of war, violence, loss and sadness. When will we learn...or perhaps, although it may be cynical...maybe this 'hate' is in fact what makes us human...

text: this movie is absolute garbage. seriously.   will smith (who I do like as an actor) sleepwalks his way through his entire performance. no inspiration and no energy. he's supposed to be a criminal with this magnetic personality, but he has less charisma than a slab of deadwood.   we're supposed to connect and care about the "love" relationship of two characters that lie to each other throughout the entire movie. i was actually hoping they would get killed at the end, as obnoxious as they were.   the plot is so convoluted and idiotic. every "brilliant heist," leaves gaping logical holes that will make you want to pull your hair out.   the only saving grace is margot robbie's performance- she's fantastic as always. but otherwise this movie is a gigantic waste of time.
